Budget Analyst, Engineering -MON19795
Description

BOMBARDIER
Bombardier is a global leader, creating innovative and game-changing planes. Our products and services provide world-class transportation experiences that set new standards in passenger comfort, energy, efficiency, reliability and safety. We are a global organization focused on working together with a team spirit.
The role of Budget Analyst, Engineering is to control, plan and manage the various budgetary aspect for the Aircraft Design and Development group. This include supporting the yearly budget planification and quarterly forecast phases, updating & tracking on weekly / monthly basis budget actual spend, reviewing & analyzing budget actual data and supporting and / or developing the required reporting tools / reports for the budget planning and tracking. You will be reporting to the Project management group of Aircraft Design & Development.
If you enjoy working in a flexible environment as part of a dynamic and autonomous team with visibility and interaction with senior management, this job is for you!
In your role, you will:
Lead weekly financial governance for Project, Engineering group;
Manage weekly/monthly budget tracking and reporting for various budget categories (Cloking hours, capitalize budget, indirect hours, other direct cost, major department expenses…);
Participate in annual budget planification and quarterly reforecast exercises;
Validate data reported in weekly/monthly Finance team reports to ensure data accuracy and to identify/resolve any discrepancies;
Analyze budget spend and give visibility to management on the risks and opportunities;
Lead and/or participate in review meeting with engineering, programs office and finance group to ensure that the budget is aligned and respected with the allocated envelopes;
Maintain, develop and/or improved Power BI reports / dashboard to provide budget status visibility to all Aircraft Design and Development groups;
Lead or participate in tools and report development to facilitate data analysis and reporting.

Qualifications

As our ideal candidate,
You have a minimum of 5 years of experience in Finances, Project Management or Business Administration;
You hold a bachelor’s degree in Finances, Engineering, Business Administration or equivalent;
You have strong financial skills with an analytical mind;
You are very rigorous with attention to details;
You demonstrate a professional attitude and superior communication skills;
You have excellent organizational and leadership skills, able to work with a minimum of supervision;
You are self-motivated, enthusiastic and results oriented;
You have very good computer skills (MS Office; Excel advanced, Power BI, SQL);
You have strong bilingual oral & written skills.
